{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"179d144a-2071-4419-bad6-12b09147b3b2","content":"In your project file, simply remove (or set to `false`) the `UseVSTest` property:\n\n```xml\n<!-- Before -->\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n  <PropertyGroup>\n    <UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n</Project>\n\n<!-- After -->\n<Project Sdk=\"MSTest.Sdk/3.8.0\">\n</Project>\n```\n\nMicrosoft.Testing.Platform is the **default** for MSTest.Sdk, so removing `<UseVSTest>true</UseVSTest>` is the only required change.\n\n**Key differences to be aware of:**\n\n| | VSTest | Microsoft.Testing.Platform |\n|---|---|---|\n| Run tests | `dotnet test` | `dotnet test` (or `dotnet run`) |\n| CLI flags | `--filter` | `--filter` still works; also supports `--treenode-filter` |\n| `.runsettings` | Fully supported | Supported, but some adapters may differ |\n\n**After switching**, run `dotnet test` to verify everything works. If you have CI scripts using VSTest-specific flags (e.g., `--logger trx`), those are still supported but check the [Microsoft.Testing.Platform docs](https://learn.microsoft.com/dotnet/core/testing/microsoft-testing-platform) for any flag differences.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"3d10d983-c58d-4b58-a6d6-1c61e0d0744a","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform in their MSTest project. This is a knowledge question about .NET testing configuration. Let me provide a concise answer based on my knowledge.\n\nWhen using MSTest.Sdk, switching from VSTest to Microsoft.Testing.Platform involves:\n\n1. Removing or setting `<UseVSTest>false</UseVSTest>` (or just removing the property, since Microsoft.Testing.Platform is the default in newer MSTest.Sdk versions)\n2. Adjusting how you run tests (using `dotnet test` or `dotnet run`)\n\nLet me give a clear, concise answer.","outputTokens":495,"requestId":"4C17:3CBB00:E14C20:1157D9C:6A0129F1"},"id":"d16d2fd4-01db-48ef-a6cd-edffa6c11d16","timestamp":"2026-05-11T00:59:39.792Z","parentId":"a42d3dab-a585-403c-be65-e8b9ea92ce84"}
